<br>
The spirit of the calendar is not about this BB thing either.  Sorry guys, don't know where the hell you got that at.  It was more like to stop others from training ya, then to stop piggy back riding. Thats the reason the calendar was made, then some rules.<br>
<br>
An hour and a half I think is enough time to get a group to three groups to go clear 15 mobs and then a god, especially if some or all of the original posting entity would be willing to help out which I'm sure a few of them would have.<br>
<br>
And if a BB guild declines a god, then it should actually be up to that BB guild to find their replacements.  Reason for this, the original guild notified who they had to, it isn't a rule to go around looking all over the server for a few groups to help them out.<br>
<br>
If your gonna ban someone from posting for 30 days, you should at least allow them to finish their posted raids, then not allow them to post for a full cycle. By doing it your way, your taking away 3 raids maybe 4, instead of the necessary 3 raids.  You would anger less people, and the lesson would still be learned.<br>
<br>
Ok something else about changes.  10 o'clock is to early to call in a BB guild.  Hell the raids basicly just starting and you don't know whats really gonna happen until later on.  12 o'clock for weekends, and maybe 11 o'clock for weekdays.  It's reasonable and allows you to actually judge if you need the BB or not.  Also if a god is up the 2am thing should be moved back, infact it should be moved back regardless.  If your there until 3 it doesn't affect the next guilds raid, probably even 4am wouldn't.  And change that word guild to posting entity, allowing items to rot is as bad if not worse than allowing a epic item to go unused.  <br>
<br>
Another thing, how many patches does the Rathe get a week.  One is guaranteed, saw two but don't know if thats a common thing or not since I'm unable to play atm, but if its two a week why do we still need this BB guild, were getting one more god a week than any other server, and thats not even including server crashes which isn't all that uncommon.  <br>
<br>
Just my opinion here, but the calendar was made for the whole server and not the BB guild thing.  It seems like this BB guild issue is destroying every noble attempt made for the calendar so trash the idea, its just getting stupid.  And banning a guild for a basicly leaving a god up just illustrates how bad its gotten, when this was first made this would have never happened.  Epics are nice, hell I want mine too, basicly get 3 of them but have none, but I don't think giving myself or a few friends a better chance at getting them is worthwhile at the expense of 50 or so other peoples fun.</font><P>  Only in death are our souls set free.<br>
